<seg id=1> The primary and secondary schools in Zhejiang typhoon-afflicted areas were reopened. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Hangzhou, 2 September, by Shen Haixong, Shen Xiquan No.17 typhoon made the educational system in Zhejian typhoon-afflicted areas sustain a serious loss. There were about 1,500 schools whose campus and facilities were damaged. </seg>
<seg id=3> Owing to the government and people's effort, at present, most of the primary and secondary schools in the areas were reopened. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The Department of Education in Zhejiang Province sent work teams to Wenzhou, Taizhou, and etc. to help the education return to normal. </seg>
<seg id=5> More than 20 leaders of the Educational Committee in Wenzhou City were divided into 7 teams and were sent to Leqing, Ouhai, Dongtou, Pingyan and etc. to help repair the campus and return the schools to normal. 20,000 Yuan of the educational expenses was used especially for the education of the typhoon-afflicted areas. </seg>
<seg id=6> In order to guarantee the students to return to the schools on time, the government offices of education in every cities, counties and towns decided to reduce or free the tuition for whose who could not afford the tuition because of the attack of typhoon. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The leaders and staff of the schools in the areas started work ahead of time to clean the campus, sterilize the school facilities and repair the school buildings. </seg>
<seg id=8> United with the Communist Youth League of Wenzhou City, Wenzhou Educational Committee organized a fundraising activity called "show your love to the schools in the disaster areas". By far, the city had raised more than 1 million Yuan. </seg>
</p>
